&lt;p&gt;When you check the box, $_POST[the name-not-id] comes back with the value.  Somewhat annoyingly (to me), checkboxes that are unchecked return nothing at all.  So, using the attend as an example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" name="attend" value="yes"&amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;would return "yes" in $_POST["attend"] when the box is checked, no value in $_POST when the box is unchecked.  So you could use several tests to see if it is checked.  For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;if (!empty($_POST["attend"])) ...
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;if (isset($_POST["attend"]) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; $_POST["attend"] === "yes") ...
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

